    "This dataset not only enriches the data source of chemical molecular structure graphs but also provides strong support for the application of graph neural networks in the field of molecular property prediction.",
    "Although the MNIST and CIFAR10 (Dwivedi et al. 2023) datasets were originally used for image classification, and they have been transformed into graph data to support graph classification tasks.",
    "This innovation not only broadens the application area of graph neural networks but also provides researchers with more diverse graph data structures to study and explore.",
    "In response to the lack of standardized, large-scale, and real-world datasets, OGB provides a large and diverse collection of benchmarking datasets, which strongly contributes to the development and application of GNN algorithms.",
    "The OGB dataset covers multiple fields from bioinformatics to social networks, and contains large-scale graph data ranging from thousands of nodes to hundreds of millions of nodes, enabling researchers to more comprehensively evaluate the performance of GNN models in real-world applications."
